---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Andorra Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/andorra/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Spain for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/spain' },
  { title: 'France for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/france' },
  { title: 'Monaco for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/monaco' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'andorraFit', header: 'Andorra Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€450-640/mo', andorraFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€525-750/mo', andorraFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€405-580/mo', andorraFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€375-535/mo', andorraFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'CASS (Andorran)', entryAge: 'All ages', renewal: 'Mandatory', monthlyFrom: '€200-300/mo', andorraFit: 'Required' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'CASS (Mandatory)', monthly: '€200-300', annual: '€2,400-3,600' },
  { category: 'Private Top-Up (65-69)', monthly: '€375-640', annual: '€4,500-7,680' },
  { category: 'Private Top-Up (70-74)', monthly: '€515-855', annual: '€6,180-10,260' },
  { category: 'Private Top-Up (75-79)', monthly: '€690-1,145', annual: '€8,280-13,740' },
  { category: 'Private Clinic Visit', monthly: '€60-120/visit', annual: 'As needed' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Andorra 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors in Andorra. Pyrenees mountain living, low taxes, excellent healthcare access to Spain/France, and coverage for retirees 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Andorra"
  subheadline="Andorra offers Pyrenees mountain beauty, low taxes, exceptional safety, skiing, and easy access to Spanish and French healthcare—a wealthy microstate ideal for active, affluent retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/andorra-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Andorra</h2>
  <p>
    Andorra offers a unique combination of Pyrenees mountain beauty, low taxes (no income tax on pensions), exceptional safety, world-class skiing, and easy access to both Spanish and French healthcare systems. For affluent active retirees seeking mountain lifestyle with tax efficiency, Andorra provides European quality without EU bureaucracy.
  </p>

  <p>
    Andorra la Vella is the capital with most services. Escaldes-Engordany offers thermal spas. All parishes offer mountain living. Barcelona is 2.5 hours away; Toulouse 2 hours. Population only 80,000—intimate community feel.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Good locally; Barcelona/Toulouse backup</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Catalan official; Spanish, French common</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> €2,500-4,000/month; higher than Spain</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Mountain; cold winters; pleasant summers</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Safe; quiet; outdoor focused</li>
      <li><strong>Tax:</strong> No income tax on foreign pensions</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Andorra Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Andorra has CASS (Caixa Andorrana de Seguretat Social)—mandatory social security covering healthcare at 75% reimbursement. Hospital Nostra Senyora de Meritxell is main facility. Good for routine care. Complex cases go to Barcelona (Hospital Clínic, Teknon) or Toulouse. Healthcare quality good but limited specialists locally.
  </p>

  <p>
    All residents must join CASS regardless of other insurance. Private insurance supplements CASS to cover copays and provide faster access. Spanish/French hospitals within 2-3 hours for specialized care.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">CASS Is Mandatory</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      All Andorran residents MUST enroll in CASS regardless of other insurance. CASS covers 75% of costs with copays for remainder. Private international insurance supplements CASS for comprehensive coverage. Budget for both mandatory CASS and private top-up.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Andorra residency options for retirees:
  </p>

  <h3>Passive Residency</h3>
  <p>
    For retirees not working. Requires €50,000 deposit with Andorran bank, proof of income (€36,000+/year), housing, and private insurance. Popular option for wealthy retirees.
  </p>

  <h3>Active Residency</h3>
  <p>
    For those with business activities. Different requirements apply.
  </p>

  <h3>Non-Lucrative Residency</h3>
  <p>
    For those living off investments. Substantial financial requirements.
  </p>

  <h3>Processing</h3>
  <p>
    Apply through Andorran Immigration. Requires local address. 183+ days/year residence required to maintain status.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Andorra:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>CASS:</strong> Mandatory for all residents</li>
    <li><strong>Private:</strong> Required for residency application</li>
    <li><strong>Coverage:</strong> Must cover Andorra and typically Spain/France</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage for Barcelona access</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Andorra</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Two-layer approach: CASS (mandatory) plus private international insurance. Private insurance should include Spain/France for specialist access. Consider global coverage since Andorra residents often travel. CASS copays can add up—private coverage reduces out-of-pocket costs.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Andorra, regional European coverage important:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Andorra</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong European network, Barcelona access</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Spain/France access:</strong> Essential for specialist care</li>
    <li><strong>CASS supplement:</strong> Covers copays and extras</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage for Andorra with Spain/France access.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Andorra (EUR):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Total Healthcare Budget</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>CASS + Private:</strong> €600-950/month total</li>
    <li><strong>Consider tax savings:</strong> No income tax on pensions</li>
    <li><strong>Barcelona option:</strong> World-class care 2.5 hours away</li>
    <li><strong>Wealthy retirees:</strong> Higher costs but tax efficient</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Skiing Enthusiast, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €4,000/month pension. Passive residency. Grandvalira skiing.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> CASS + Cigna Global with skiing coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~€700/month total. Active lifestyle; Barcelona backup for any injuries.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Tax-Efficient Retiree, 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £80,000/year pension. UK escape. Escaldes-Engordany.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> CASS + BUPA Global comprehensive.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~€850/month total. Tax savings offset higher insurance; global coverage.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Couple, Mountain Lovers, Both 69</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €6,000/month combined. Passive residency. Hiking focused.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> CASS + Allianz Care couple plan.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~€1,200/month combined. Mountain lifestyle; comprehensive coverage.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Andorra expensive?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Moderately—higher than Spain but no income tax on pensions. Property expensive. Daily costs similar to France. For high earners, tax savings can offset higher living costs. Not budget destination.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need to speak Catalan?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Helpful but not essential—Spanish and French widely spoken. Healthcare available in all three languages plus English in private clinics. Catalan is official but multilingual society.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I access Spanish hospitals?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes with private insurance—Barcelona hospitals (Teknon, Clínic, Quirónsalud) are 2.5 hours away. CASS doesn't cover Spain directly. International insurance essential for cross-border care.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's the residency deposit?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        €50,000 deposit with Andorran bank for passive residency—refundable if you leave. Plus proof of €36,000+ annual income. Financial requirements significant. Not for budget retirees.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Andorra coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Andorra residency requirements and CASS regulations change. Always verify current requirements with Andorran authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
